25/05/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The junior partner in Albania's ruling coalition, the Christian Democrat Party (CDP), announced it will hold an extraordinary congress on 3 June. A press statement Wednesday (24 May) confirmed that delegates will elect a successor to party chairman Nikoll Lesi, who has decided to step down. Nard Ndoka, a newcomer to CDP, is seen as the most likely candidate. (Albanian News - 25/05/06) 
